      "en": "This function is identical to the fcntl() function, except that the argument handling is even more complicated. The request parameter is limited to values that can fit in 32-bits or 64-bits, depending on the platform. Additional constants of interest for use as the request argument can be found in the termios module, under the same names as used in the relevant C header files. The parameter arg can be an integer, a bytes-like object, or a string. The type and size of arg must match the type a..."
